snippet.textDisplay: Video's are getting better and better man. I like the Summer better then the Winter. But I like doing cold weather stuff. I've tried Ice Swimming and typically try it every year. I also used to walk outside during the Winter months here in, Ottawa, Ontario, Canada in -20/-40'c Celcius weather. Which is very, very cold. I used to walk with just a brown undershirt on, brown cordeuroy pants and winter boots. I used to walk for 2-3 hours at a time just to see if I could do it. I was always told, I couldn't do it and from a very young age like everyoneeee else I was told by my parents and just about everyone else, you NEED to put a Winter Coat, Hat/Toque, Gloves/Mitts and a Scarf on or you will catch a cold/Pneumonia and die. I used to develop real feelings based on assumptions and just impulsively conclude thing's were true without questioning them. There came a point in my life when I started to question everyyy single thing word for word and that's when I started to learn and really perceive thing's correctly. One of the many thing's I questioned was if I COULD, Swim during the Winter and if I could walk Miles at a time in -20'c + weather. At first it was actually very scary and in truth I ALMOST gave up. But gradually as time went on I realized through HONEST REFLECTION, HEY this is actually fun and do able. In fact I even started to enjoy myself and persevered and started to love it so much I just kept challenging myself to the point where I REALIZED WOW, this isn't even a question or a challenge anymore. I can do it! I used to lay down in the snow in just a undershirt, no hat or toque, no winter coat etc. The thing ppl should realize is YES, it is very cold, but CHILL out, relax, enjoy and embrace it. You're not gonna dye, purposely misspelled. Just allow yourself to get used to it and eventually your body DOES Aclimatize. That's what smart ppl have realized and that's how ppl enjoy it! Ok awesome vids! Looking forward to the next one.

Forbes published a report titled “Will We Get To The Bottom Of The Truth On Forced Organ Removal In China?” by Ewelina U. Ochab on March 21, 2019.


Reenactment of the Chinese Communist Party's state-sanctioned organ harvesting from living Falun Gong practitioners in Hong Kong on January 12, 2013.

The Forbes article began by mentioning the UN International Day for the Right to the Truth Concerning Gross Human Rights Violations and for the Dignity of Victims.

The author went on to describe the Chinese Communist Party's (CCP) state-sanctioned organ harvesting from living prisoners of conscience, “Over recent years, several researchers (including lawyers and investigators) have been raising the issue of forced organ removal in China, namely, the illegal practice of removing organs from individuals who did not consent to it.”
